
[1]barbarity

   BARBAR'ITY, n. [See Barbarian.] The manners of a barbarian; savageness;
   cruelty; ferociousness; inhumanity.

   2. Barbarism; impurity of speech. [The use of the word in this sense,
   is now superseded by barbarism.]
